member.example:
Given a record with keys a, b, c, d, e, f and g, the following code will map the record to an object with properties
a of type int, b of type string, c of type bool, d of type double, e of type long, f of type float and g of type decimal:

var record = ...; // obtain a record somehow
var result = record.AsObject(
    (int a, string b, bool c, double d, long e, float f, decimal g) =>
        new { a, b, c, d, e, f, g });

Given a record with keys a, b, c, d, e, f, g and h, the following code will map the record to an object with properties
a of type int, b of type string, c of type bool, d of type double, e of type long, f of type float, g of type decimal and h of type byte:

var record = ...; // obtain a record somehow
var result = record.AsObject(
    (int a, string b, bool c, double d, long e, float f, decimal g, byte h) =>
        new { a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h });

Given a record with keys a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h and i, the following code will map the record to an object with properties
a of type int, b of type string, c of type bool, d of type double, e of type long, f of type float, g of type decimal, h of type byte and i of type short:

var record = ...; // obtain a record somehow
var result = record.AsObject(
    (int a, string b, bool c, double d, long e, float f, decimal g, byte h, short i) =>
        new { a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h, i });

Given a record with keys a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h, i and j, the following code will map the record to an object with properties
a of type int, b of type string, c of type bool, d of type double, e of type long, f of type float, g of type decimal, h of type byte, i of type short and j of type ushort:

var record = ...; // obtain a record somehow
var result = record.AsObject(
    (int a, string b, bool c, double d, long e, float f, decimal g, byte h, short i, ushort j) =>
        new { a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h, i, j });

member.summary:
As of 5.15, the driver has migrated the underlying message reading mechanism utilizing ;
this optimizes the reading and memory usage of the driver, and setting this to true will revert the driver to
the legacy message reader.
